---
import Button from "./Button.astro";
---

<section class="max-w-[1440px] mx-auto px-5 md:px-[40px] mt-[60px] md:mt-[100px]" id="health-check">
  <!-- Top panel -->
  <div class="bg-green rounded-[6px] px-6 md:px-[60px] lg:px-[115px] py-[40px] md:py-[76px] text-center">
    <h2 class="font-tight text-[36px] md:text-[64px] lg:text-[96px] leading-[1.1] uppercase text-dark mb-[40px] md:mb-[94px]">
      Small shifts,<br />big difference
    </h2>
    <p class="font-tight text-[22px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[48px] leading-[1.15] uppercase text-dark max-w-[1130px] mx-auto">
      Two minutes now could make a big difference later. Our Health Check is a quick way to see whether your KiwiSaver is roughly on track, or whether it might be time for a proper look. It is fast, easy, and a good place to start if you want a better feel for where things are at.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-[40px] md:mt-[60px]">
      <Button label="CHECK MY FUND" href="#health-check" />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Intro text -->
  <div class="bg-cream border-[6px] border-dark rounded-[6px] px-6 md:px-[60px] lg:px-[115px] py-[30px] md:py-[52px] text-center mt-[20px]">
    <p class="font-tight text-[22px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[48px] leading-[1.35] uppercase text-dark max-w-[1130px] mx-auto">
      Let's have a look at 3% difference in annual returns on a $50,000 balance with 3.5% employee + 3.5% employer contributions over 20 years...
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Comparison cards -->
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-[21px] mt-[20px]">
    <div class="bg-white border-[6px] border-dark rounded-[6px] px-6 md:px-[55px] py-[40px] md:py-[86px]">
      <p class="font-tight text-[22px] md:text-[28px] lg:text-[36px] leading-[1.5] uppercase text-dark mb-[40px] md:mb-[86px]">
        A POOR performing fund gets you:
      </p>
      <p class="font-narrow text-[56px] md:text-[80px] lg:text-[110px] leading-[1] uppercase text-dark tracking-[-1.1px]">
        $340,606
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-white border-[6px] border-dark rounded-[6px] px-6 md:px-[55px] py-[40px] md:py-[86px]">
      <p class="font-tight text-[22px] md:text-[28px] lg:text-[36px] leading-[1.5] uppercase text-dark mb-[40px] md:mb-[86px]">
        A TOP performing fund gets you:
      </p>
      <p class="font-narrow text-[56px] md:text-[80px] lg:text-[110px] leading-[1] uppercase text-dark tracking-[-1.1px]">
        $530,905
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Difference highlight -->
  <div class="bg-yellow rounded-[6px] px-6 md:px-[60px] lg:px-[115px] py-[40px] md:py-[86px] text-center mt-[20px]">
    <p class="font-narrow text-[56px] md:text-[80px] lg:text-[110px] leading-[1] uppercase text-dark tracking-[-1.1px] mb-[30px] md:mb-[50px]">
      $190,000
    </p>
    <p class="font-tight text-[22px] md:text-[36px] lg:text-[48px] leading-[1.35] uppercase text-dark max-w-[1130px] mx-auto">
      Difference, just from being with the right fund and provider
    </p>
    <p class="font-tight text-[12px] md:text-[14px] lg:text-[16px] leading-[1.5] uppercase text-dark/60 max-w-[1130px] mx-auto mt-[20px] md:mt-[35px]">
      *Illustrative example based on a $50,000 starting balance, 3.5% employee + 3.5% employer contributions on a $70,000 salary, comparing 6% vs 9% average annual returns after fees, over 20 years. Actual results will vary.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
